      ],
      "content": "Document state in Powerhouse is organized into scopes:\n\n- **Global scope** (`state.global`): Synchronized data that lives on a Reactor or remote server. This is where your document's main content belongs. Most use cases work exclusively with `state.global`.\n- **Local scope** (`state.local`): For edge cases where data should only exist on the local device and not sync.\n\nA future **authorization scope** is planned for permission-controlled data.\n\nWhen accessing document state in editors, you use `selectedDocument.state.global.items` (for example). Operations are also scoped - `document.operations.global` contains the operation history for the global scope.",
